text: Michael Richey may refer to: * Michael Richey (scholar) (1678–1761), German scholar and poet, set the verses to Telemanns Admiralitätsmusik * Michael Richey (sailor) (1917–2009), English sailor, first director of the Royal Institute of Navigation, winner of the John Llewellyn Rhys Prize 1942 * David Michael Richey (1938–2015), real name of the American jazz musician Slim Richey
title: Michael Richey
